-- NZ Employers Advertised for More Skilled Workers in June, Government Says
-- Tracy Withers
-- 2010-07-18T22:51:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-18/nz-employers-advertised-for-more-skilled-workers-in-june-government-says.html

          
          
             New Zealand employers advertised
for more skilled workers in June, according to a government
report.  
 Demand for skilled workers rose 10 percent in the three
months ended June 30, Employment Minister Paula Bennett said in
a statement, citing an index published by the Department of
Labour. The index is based on vacancies posted on the nationâ€™s
three largest recruitment Web sites.  
          
          


  


        